ich aspires to \"Leave no one behind in the digital age\".</p>\r\n\r\n<p>UNCDF will use a selection process in 2 waves in November 2020 and April 2021:</p>\r\n<p>For more information on this call, pleasevisit the followinglink:</p>\r\n<p>\r\n<a href=\"https://www.uncdf.org/article/6286/rfa-challenge-rgional-innovations-numriques-pour-lacclration-des-objectifs-de-dveloppement-durable\">https://www.uncdf.org/article/6286/rfa-challenge-rgional-innovations-numriques-pour-lacclration-des-objectifs-de-dveloppement-durable</a>\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n[/bloc-toogle-div]\r\n\r\n\r\n[bloc-toogle-div titre=\"Madagascar Financial Inclusion Project (Projet d’Inclusion Financiere à Madagascar - PIFM)\"]\r\n\r\n\r\n<p>The Malagasy Governmentsigned a Credit Agreement worth 31,600,000 DTS, equivalent to US$45,000,000, with the International Development Association (IDA) - World Bank to finance the Madagascar Financial Inclusion Project (PIFM - 6189 MG) on April 19, 2018. The projectwasimplemented on September 28, 2018.  The closing date of the projectisscheduled for July 31, 2022.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The Project Development Objective (PDP) is to \"promote the financial inclusion of individuals and MSMEs in Madagascar\" notablybyincreasing the use of transaction accounts and access to credit for MSMEs.</p>\r\n\r\n\r\n<p>The Project isimplementedthrough four (4) main components: (i) digitization of payments to increase the use of transaction accounts; (ii) access to credit for micro, small and medium enterprises (MSMEs); (iii) project management and impact assessment; and (iv) emergency responsecontingency.</p>\r\n<p>Component 1 supports the digitization of payments to increase the use of transaction accounts, through :\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>- digitization of governmentpaymentsthrough the payment of teachers\' salaries and scholarships and sometaxrevenues;</li>\r\n<li>- digitization of microfinance institutions (MFIs) through the integration of MFIs\' mobile services and the implementation of a shared MFI information and management system (MIS); and</li>\r\n<li>- creation of an environmentconducive to the increased use of transaction accountsthrough the modernization of paymentsystems infrastructure and a financialeducationcampaign.\r\nComponent 2 supports access to credit for MSMEsthrough : </li>\r\n<li>- Support for more credit provision to MSMEs by increasing the capital of partial credit portfolio guaranteefunds and an innovation fund for FINTECH solutions;</li>\r\n<li>- Supportingloan applications by setting up enterprisedevelopment services (EDS) for MSMEs and expanding MFI branches to underservedareas; and</li>\r\n<li>- Creating an enablingenvironment for access to credit for MSMEsthrough the establishment of an electronicregistry of centralizedguarantees and the improvement of the consumer protection framework.</li>\r\nComponent 3 will finance the operating costs and the impact study of the component on increasing the use of transaction accountsthroughgovernmentpayments.\r\nComponent 4 willallow the rapidreallocation of projectfunds in the event of a natural or man-made disaster or crisiscausing or likely to cause an imminent major negativeeconomic and/or social impact.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n[/bloc-toogle-div]','Ongoing project','','inherit','closed','closed','','353-revision-v1','','','2021-07-13 09:21:08','2021-07-13 07:21:08','',353,'http://192.168.0.199/CNFI/353-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(1058,1,'2021-07-13 09:23:15','2021-07-13 07:23:15','[bloc-toogle-div titre=\"CHALLENGE UNCDF\" class=\"blocToggleone\" show=\"show\"]\r\n<p style=\"text-align:center;font-weight:bold\">Call for Innovators in Africa</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align:center;font-weight:bold\">Digital innovations for ODD acceleration</p>\r\n\r\n<p>\r\nAs part of itsstrategy for the development of inclusive digital economies, UNCDF isorganizing a regional challenge \"Digital Innovations \r\nfor AcceleratingSustainableDevelopment Goals (SDGs)\" to identify high-impact, inclusive inno